/i>’, a personal name meaning ‘chief of harvest’. The Irish name was first Anglicized as <b>Mullover</b>, which was later assimilated to <i>Milford</i>. See also   Palmer  ."]},{"name":"Palmiere","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Dante, Enrico, Nicola, Salvatore, Vittorio.","Italian: from <i>palmiere</i> ‘palmer, pilgrim’. See   Palmer  ."]},{"name":"Parmer","meanings":["English: variant of   Palmer  .","Indian (northern states): variant of   Parmar  ."]},{"name":"Palmore","meanings":["Probably an altered form of English   Palmer   or an Americanized form of South German   Balmer  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Ann","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Anne .  In the U.S. <i>Ann</i> is the more frequent spelling."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Ann Palmer was born in 1510, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with John Gower. She died in 1568, in Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1510–1568":"1510–1568","1510–1570":"1510–1570","1530–1567":"1530–1567","1568":"1568","1567":"1567","1510":"1510","1530":"1530","1570":"1570","Guildford, Surrey, England":"Guildford, Surrey, England","Towcester, Northamptonshire, , England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1510–1568":"1510–1568","1510–1570":"1510–1570","1530–1567":"1530–1567","1568":"1568","1567":"1567","1510":"1510","1530":"1530","1570":"1570","Guildford, Surrey, England":"Guildford, Surrey, England","Towcester, Northamptonshire, , England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"